.TH JSSCLI 1 "2026-07-18" "jsscli 0.5.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jsscli \- JSON\-first CLI for the JSS / Frappe REST API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jsscli
[\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-v\fR...]
[\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIoptions\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jsscli
is a fast, secure, and scriptable command\-line client for any Frappe/ERPNext
or Juragan Subsystem site. It provides full access to REST resources, custom
server methods, file operations, and document attachments, with a consistent
JSON output and built\-in session management.

All output is JSON. When stdout is a terminal, the JSON is colourised and
indented; when piped or redirected, plain pretty\-printed JSON is used.
Errors are also printed as JSON to stderr, making integration with shell
pipelines and automation tools straightforward.

Sensitive credentials (passwords, API secrets) are stored in the system
keyring; session data is encrypted at rest using AES‑256‑GCM with a key
derived via HKDF and a random salt.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress non\-error messages printed to stderr (e.g., progress hints).
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase log verbosity (can be repeated). Affects internal logging only;
does not change JSON output.
.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR
Use the specified account profile instead of the active account. Overrides
the \fBJSS_PROFILE\fR environment variable.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS auth
Manage authentication for the active account.
.TP
\fBjsscli auth login\fR
Authenticate using stored credentials. On success, a session is saved
locally and reused by subsequent commands. Output example:
.RS
{"ok":true, "account":"prod", "full_name":"John Doe", "sitename":"mysite", "roles":["System Manager"]}
.RE
.TP
\fBjsscli auth logout\fR
End the server session and remove the local session record.
.TP
\fBjsscli auth status\fR
Show whether a valid session exists for the active account.
.TP
\fBjsscli auth whoami\fR
Display the full name, sitename, and roles of the authenticated user.
.SS account
Manage named account profiles. Account definitions are stored in
\fI~/.config/jsscli/accounts.toml\fR; secrets are kept in the system keyring.
.TP
\fBjsscli account add\fR \fIname\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Create a new account.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-url\fR \fIURL\fR
(Required) Base URL of the Frappe site (e.g., https://mysite.example.com).
.TP
\fB\-\-mode\fR \fBsession\fR|\fBtoken\fR
Authentication mode (default: \fBsession\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-email\fR \fIemail\fR
Required for session mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-password\fR \fIpass\fR
Password; if omitted you will be prompted securely.
.TP
\fB\-\-api\-key\fR \fIkey\fR
Required for token mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-api\-secret\fR \fIsec\fR
Required for token mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-sitename\fR \fIname\fR
Expected site name (optional; used for validation).
.TP
\fB\-\-activate\fR
Set this account as active immediately.
.RE
.TP
\fBjsscli account list\fR
List all accounts; active one is marked with \fBactive:true\fR.
.TP
\fBjsscli account use\fR \fIname\fR
Switch the active account to \fIname\fR.
.TP
\fBjsscli account remove\fR \fIname\fR
Delete an account and all associated secrets.
.TP
\fBjsscli account show\fR [\fIname\fR]
Show detailed information for an account (secrets are masked).
.SS config
.TP
\fBjsscli config set\fR \fIkey\fR \fIvalue\fR
Set a configuration key. Special key \fBactive_account\fR sets the active
account (same as \fBaccount use\fR).
.TP
\fBjsscli config get\fR \fIkey\fR
Print the value of a configuration key.
.TP
\fBjsscli config list\fR
List all current settings.
.TP
\fBjsscli config init\fR
Create the configuration directory and default files.
.TP
\fBjsscli config path\fR
Print the absolute path to the configuration file.
.SS doctype
Perform CRUD operations on any DocType.
.TP
\fBjsscli doctype get\fR \fIdoctype\fR \fIname\fR
Retrieve a single document. Output contains a top\-level \fB"data"\fR key.
.TP
\fBjsscli doctype list\fR \fIdoctype\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
List documents matching filters.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-fields\fR \fIf1,f2,...\fR
Comma\-separated list of fields to return.
.TP
\fB\-\-filter\fR \fIfield,op,value\fR
Filter condition (e.g., \fBstatus,=,Active\fR). Can be repeated.
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIn\fR
Maximum number of records (default: 20).
.TP
\fB\-\-start\fR \fIn\fR
Offset for pagination.
.TP
\fB\-\-order\-by\fR \fIfield\fR
Sort field (append \fB desc\fR for descending order).
.RE
.TP
\fBjsscli doctype create\fR \fIdoctype\fR [\fIfile\fR]
Create a new document. Data is read from a JSON file (or stdin if \fIfile\fR
is \fB\-\fR).
.TP
\fBjsscli doctype update\fR \fIdoctype\fR \fIname\fR [\fIfile\fR]
Update an existing document using JSON from \fIfile\fR (or stdin).
.TP
\fBjsscli doctype delete\fR \fIdoctype\fR \fIname\fR [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
Delete a document. Confirmation is required unless \fB\-y\fR is supplied.
.SS file
Manage files and attachments.
.TP
\fBjsscli file upload\fR \fIfile\fR \fIdoctype\fR \fIdocname\fR \fIfieldname\fR
Upload a local file (max 50 MB) and attach it to the specified document.
.TP
\fBjsscli file download\fR \fIurl\fR [\fB\-o\fR \fIpath\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
Download a file from a relative URL (e.g., \fI/files/report.pdf\fR). If no
\fB\-o\fR is given, the file is saved in the current directory with the
basename from the URL.
.TP
\fBjsscli file list\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
List files from a folder (default: \fBHome\fR) with flexible filters.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-folder\fR \fIpath\fR
Folder to list (default: "Home").
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIn\fR
Maximum number of files (default: 50).
.TP
\fB\-\-search\fR \fIpattern\fR
Filter by file name (substring match).
.TP
\fB\-\-file\-type\fR \fIpattern\fR
Filter by file MIME type (substring match).
.TP
\fB\-\-attached\-to\-doctype\fR \fIdoctype\fR
Filter by linked document type.
.TP
\fB\-\-attached\-to\-name\fR \fIdocname\fR
Filter by linked document name.
.RE
.SS attachments
.TP
\fBjsscli attachments\fR \fIdoctype\fR \fIname\fR
Scan a document for file attachments (fields with values like
\fI/private/files/...\fR or \fI/files/...\fR). A list of files is displayed
and you are prompted to download all, cancel, or select specific files by
index (e.g., \fB1,3\fR).
.SS files
.TP
\fBjsscli files\fR \fInumber\fR
Convenience command that accepts a single identifier:
.RS
.IP \(bu
If \fInumber\fR starts with "ODR\-", it is treated as a \fBData Pengajuan\fR
document name.
.IP \(bu
Otherwise, it is treated as a \fIno_perjanjian\fR (loan agreement number); the
corresponding \fBMaster Data Nasabah\fR record is fetched to obtain its
\fBregister_id\fR, and then attachments from the \fBData Pengajuan\fR
doctype with that ID are listed.
.PP
The attachment download prompt is then shown, identical to
\fBattachments\fR.
.RE
.SS call\-method
.TP
\fBjsscli call\-method\fR \fImethod.path\fR [\fB\-\-args\fR \fIkey=val,key=val...\fR]
Call any server\-side Python method. Arguments are passed as a JSON object.
This command is the Swiss army knife for executing custom logic, lazy\-loaded
child tables, workspace queries, and reports.
.RS
.PP
Examples:
.br
\fBjsscli call\-method\fR "juragan.ops...get_lazy_child_rows" \fB\-\-args\fR docname=OD\-...,tab=informasi_bpkb_tab
.br
\fBjsscli call\-method\fR "frappe.desk.query_report.run" \fB\-\-args\fR report_name=Stok_TTS,filters={}
.RE
.SS search
.TP
\fBjsscli search\fR \fIquery\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Perform a global search across all DocTypes.
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIn\fR
Maximum number of results (default: 20).
.TP
\fB\-\-doctype\fR \fIdoctype\fR
Restrict search to a specific DocType.
.RE
.SS tunggakan
.TP
\fBjsscli tunggakan\fR \fIno_rekening_kredit\fR
Retrieve the detailed outstanding debt breakdown for a given credit account
number. This calls the server method
\fIjuragan.ops.doctype.master_data_nasabah.master_data_nasabah.cek_rincian_hutang_nasabah\fR
and returns its JSON response. Useful for obtaining the raw data before
generating the printable "Kartu Piutang".
.SS kp
.TP
\fBjsscli kp\fR \fIno_perjanjian\fR
Generate and download the "Form Rincian Sisa Piutang Nasabah" PDF
(receivable card) for a given loan agreement number.
.RS
.PP
The command performs the following steps:
.IP 1.
Find the customer record in \fBMaster Data Nasabah\fR using \fIno_perjanjian\fR.
.IP 2.
Extract \fBno_rekening_kredit\fR (credit account number) and the document name.
.IP 3.
Call the server method \fBcek_rincian_hutang_nasabah\fR with the account
number to ensure the receivable data is computed on the server.
.IP 4.
Download the PDF using the print format "Form Rincian Sisa Piutang Nasabah"
(without letterhead).
.IP 5.
Save the PDF in the system's \fBDownloads\fR folder with a filename like
\fIRincian_Sisa_Piutang_<agreement>.pdf\fR.
.PP
If the server method fails or the receivable data is still not available,
the PDF will contain a placeholder message. Ensure the customer has
outstanding data before running this command.
.RE
.SS info
.TP
\fBjsscli info\fR
Print detailed build and version information, including Git hash, branch,
commit count, build timestamp, compiler versions, and target platform.
This data is embedded at compile time and does not require network access.
.SS changelog
.TP
\fBjsscli changelog\fR [\fB\-n\fR \fIcount\fR]
Display the Git commit history embedded at build time (up to 50 commits).
If the binary was built outside a Git repository, an empty list is returned.
.SS manual
.TP
\fBjsscli manual\fR
Open the built\-in manual in a terminal pager (scrollable, searchable).
Press \fBq\fR to quit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBJSS_PROFILE\fR
Name of the account profile to use (overridden by \fB\-\-profile\fR).
.TP
\fBJSS_EMAIL\fR
Default email when adding a session\-based account.
.TP
\fBJSS_ACTIVE_ACCOUNT\fR
Overrides the \fBactive_account\fR setting in \fIconfig.toml\fR.
.PP
Standard proxy variables (\fBHTTPS_PROXY\fR, \fBHTTP_PROXY\fR, \fBNO_PROXY\fR)
are respected by the underlying HTTP client.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.config/jsscli/config.toml\fR
Global settings (active account, defaults).
.TP
\fI~/.config/jsscli/accounts.toml\fR
Account definitions (no secrets).
.TP
\fI~/.cache/jsscli/session.enc\fR
Encrypted session data.
.TP
\fI~/.cache/jsscli/.session.salt\fR
Salt file for encryption key derivation.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Generic runtime error (e.g., I/O, parse error).
.TP
2
Invalid usage or input.
.TP
3
Not authenticated (no valid session).
.TP
4
Network error (connection, timeout).
.TP
5
API error (non\-2xx HTTP response from server).
.SH EXAMPLES
Add an account and log in:
.PP
.RS
\fBjsscli account add prod \-\-url https://frappe.example.com \-\-email admin@example.com \-\-activate\fR
.br
\fBjsscli auth login\fR
.RE
.PP
List active customers:
.RS
\fBjsscli doctype list "Master Data Nasabah" \-\-filter status,=,Aktif \-\-fields name,nama_nasabah,no_perjanjian \-\-limit 10\fR
.RE
.PP
Download all attachments from a loan agreement:
.RS
\fBjsscli files 6001\-0000053\-0001\fR
.br
(then select \fBy\fR to download all files)
.RE
.PP
Search for documents containing "VIXION":
.RS
\fBjsscli search VIXION \-\-doctype "Master Data Nasabah" \-\-limit 5\fR
.RE
.PP
Check outstanding debt details:
.RS
\fBjsscli tunggakan 6001\-0000053\-0001\fR
.RE
.PP
Generate the receivable card PDF:
.RS
\fBjsscli kp 6001\-0000053\-0001\fR
.RE
.PP
Call a custom server method:
.RS
\fBjsscli call\-method "juragan.collection.utils.get_combined_collection_data" \fR
\fB\-\-args date_from=2026\-07\-01,date_to=2026\-07\-31\fR
.RE
.PP
Show build information:
.RS
\fBjsscli info\fR
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR librjss (3),
.BR frappe (7)
.br
Frappe REST API documentation: \fIhttps://frappeframework.com/docs\fR
